.TH "ocs_aes_op" 9 "ocs_aes_op" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ocs_aes_op \- Perform AES/SM4 operation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ocs_aes_op
.BI "(struct ocs_aes_dev *aes_dev "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_mode mode "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_cipher cipher "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_instruction instruction "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dst_dma_list "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t src_dma_list "  ","
.BI "u32 src_size "  ","
.BI "u8 *iv "  ","
.BI "u32 iv_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aes_dev" 12
The OCS AES device to use.
.IP "mode" 12
The mode to use (ECB, CBC, CTR, or CTS).
.IP "cipher" 12
The cipher to use (AES or SM4).
.IP "instruction" 12
The instruction to perform (encrypt or decrypt).
.IP "dst_dma_list" 12
The OCS DMA list mapping output memory.
.IP "src_dma_list" 12
The OCS DMA list mapping input payload data.
.IP "src_size" 12
The amount of data mapped by \fIsrc_dma_list\fP.
.IP "iv" 12
The IV vector.
.IP "iv_size" 12
The size (in bytes) of \fIiv\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
